Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Halve the @sweet potato{2} lengthways and pop them
on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Rub the oil into the potatoes then lay them skin-side down on the
baking tray. Roast on the top shelf of your oven until tender and the knife
slips in easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat.
When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{240%g} and cook until browned,
~{2-3%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw
mince. Use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. While it cooks, drain
and rinse the @red kidney beans{1} in a #sieve{}.

Drain and discard any excess fat from the beef, then season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Add the @Central American style spice mix{1} and roughly squish half
of the kidney beans with your hands (to break them up). Stir in the remaining
kidney beans, @tomato passata{1}, @beef stock paste{10%g}, @water for the beans{50%ml}
and @sugar for the sauce{1/2%tsp} (see ingredients for both amounts).

Bring the mixture to the boil, then cover with a #lid{}, turn the heat to low
and leave to cook slowly for the same amount of time your potato needs. In the
meantime, put your feet up. IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink
in the middle.

Once everything is ready, taste the chilli and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if you
feel it needs it.

Serve the jacket sweet potato halves on #plates{} with the chilli spooned on
top. Grate over the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g} at the table and use #scissors{}
to snip the @chives{1} over the top. Enjoy!